description:
Mike Wolfer's Razor opus from the pages of Threshold is now available in this special expanded square bound edition that features lots of all-new, ultra-spicy pages! It is Razor as you have never seen her before, with Lethal Stryke and Poizon thrown into the mix as they face off against Widow and Pandora! But the stakes are higher than ever as Razor gets infected with the spidervirus and will spread it to whomever she breeds with! It is sultry catfight action as Spider-Razor and Widow get into the arachnafight of the century! You don't want to miss this final volume of the ultimate Razor story.

This issue reprints Threshold #42-44 and contains several new pages.
name: Doomsday Run 4-6
En mai, fais ce qu'il te plait

description: Fearing to be on the losing end of a coming war, Pandora funds a cloning experiment on a remote tropical island. After several failed clones, Anna Martelli has given the scientists a tissue sample of Pandora herself. The resulting clone is called Shimmer. Suddenly, the base is overrun by H&K agents. Anna quickly programs Shimmer to protect her. Shimmer kills most H&K agents before Anna is knocked out during the fight. When she regains consciousness, Shimmer is gone.
name: One-Shot

description: Two special stories in this final harrowing issue! One the most popular horror novel writers, Joe R. Lansdale, is unleashed in this all-new series that adapts some of his favorite short stories, all chosen by Lansdale himself, into comic form for the first time. This issue sees the Indian artist Dheeraj Verma, bring the tale "God of the Razor" to sequential life! A second tale illustrated by Verma is also included, "My Dead Dog, Bobby". It's Lansdale, so you know people die in really bad ways. Available in regular and wraparound covers by Burrows.
name: God of the Razor / My Dead Dog, Bobby
Night They Missed the Horror Show

description: With the cruel Caster now in control of the powerful Saber, the situation has turned bleak for the remaining Masters. But right when all the cards seem to have fallen into Caster's hands, Berserker decimates her base, leaving her open to attack from Tosaka and Archer! Will a chilling revelation about Archer's true identity put a stop to their assault...or will the honors go to Saber?
name: Volume 8
